<plot>Gene Kelly's first TV special finds him dancing with three European ballerinas; performing with two youngsters, Liza Minnelli &amp; Cherylene Lee from "Flower Drum Song;" and dancing to a Carl Sandburg's "A Poem To Dance To," written for this show. Nelson Riddle contributes an original composition called "Jam Session" which serves as a production number.</plot><url>http://localhost:8983/solr/movie.html?559998</url></doc>
